家具の固定や配置の確認、非常持ち出し品の点検など、今日という日に改めて「地震への備え」の確認を。
text_en:
It's been 28 years since the #Hanshin Awaji Earthquake.
There is a possibility that a large earthquake will occur in Nagano Prefecture.
What you can do is "prepare" for an earthquake that you do not know when it will occur.
Today is the day to reconfirm your "earthquake preparation", such as confirming the fixing and arrangement of furniture, and checking emergency take-out items.

@hibiki_smtn 今日は阪神淡路大震災の日でしたね。

地元の兵庫県明石の被害は神戸に比べたら大丈夫だったみたいです。

親戚のおばさんが住んでた神戸市灘区は壊滅状態でした。

そんな大地震がいつ来るかわからないので・・後悔しないように今を精一杯生きなきゃって思いました。
text_en:
@hibiki_smtn Today was the day of the Great Hanshin-Awaji Earthquake.

It seems that the damage in the local Akashi, Hyogo Prefecture was okay compared to Kobe.

Nada Ward, Kobe City, where my relative's aunt lived, was in a state of destruction.

I don't know when such a big earthquake will come, so I thought I had to live as hard as I could so that I wouldn't regret it.

one-storied house
big brother

94年、神戸文化ホールから「来年、中ホールで公演しませんか」とオファー来たけど震災で中止。
中ホールも避難所になって、それが解除されてから無理に自主公演した。900席に観客50人。大赤字。

text_en:
In 1994, I received an offer from Kobe Bunka Hall saying, "Would you like to perform at the middle hall next year?"
The middle hall became an evacuation center, and after the restrictions were lifted, I forced myself to perform independently. 50 spectators in 900 seats. Big deficit.
After the performance, the theater staff said, "Thank you Hishida-san. You don't have to pay the theater fee."
I cried for the first time after the earthquake. https://t.co/jk4JlNkFep

それまで、地震に備えるという話で出てくる体験談が「関東大震災」という遠い出来事だったのを、差し替えたのが阪神淡路大地震で、今はそれが東日本大震災に置き換わってるわけだが、
そういえば、その間に存在する1944.12.7東南海地震って、記録があまりないせいか話題にならんな
text_en:
Until then, the experience story that appeared in the story of preparing for an earthquake was a distant event called the "Great Kanto Earthquake", but it was replaced by the Great Hanshin Awaji Earthquake, and now it has been replaced by the Great East Japan Earthquake.
Come to think of it, the 1944.12.7 Tonankai earthquake, which exists in between, is not a topic of discussion, probably because there are not many records.

Today marks the 28th anniversary of the Great Hanshin-Awaji earthquake that devastated many towns in central Japan. The most affected was Kobe, with thousands of deaths and the city suffered innumerable damage.

Today is a day to remember those who left🕯️ https://t.co/Hru29g1up2
